{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 2 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:1",
      "text": "These are the names of the sons of Israel;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:2",
      "text": "Ruben, Symeon, Levi, Juda, Issachar, Zabulon, Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Nephthali, Gad, Aser.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:3",
      "text": "The sons of Juda; Er, Aunan, Selom. These three were born to him of the daughter of Sava the Chananitish woman: and Er, the first-born of Juda, was wicked before the Lord, and he slew him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:4",
      "text": "And Thamar his daughter-in-law bore to him Phares, and Zara: all the sons of Juda were five.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:5",
      "text": "The sons of Phares, Esrom, and Jemuel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:6",
      "text": "And the sons of Zara, Zambri, and Ætham, and Æmuan, and Calchal, and Darad, in all five.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:7",
      "text": "And the sons of Charmi; Achar the troubler of Israel, who was disobedient in the accursed thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:8",
      "text": "And the sons of Ætham; Azarias,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:9",
      "text": "and the sons of Esrom who were born to him; Jerameel, and Aram, and Chaleb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:10",
      "text": "And Aram begot Aminadab, and Aminadab begot Naasson, chief of the house of Juda.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:11",
      "text": "And Naasson begot Salmon, and Salmon begot Booz,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:12",
      "text": "and Booz begot Obed, and Obed begot Jessae.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:13",
      "text": "And Jessae begot his first-born Eliab, Aminadab was the second, Samaa the third,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:14",
      "text": "Nathanael the fourth, Zabdai the fifth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:15",
      "text": "Asam the sixth, David the seventh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:16",
      "text": "And their sister was Saruia, and another Abigaia: and the sons of Saruia were Abisa, and Joab, and Asael, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:17",
      "text": "And Abigaia bore Amessab: and the father of Amessab was Jothor the Ismaelite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:18",
      "text": "And Chaleb the son of Esrom took Gazuba to wife, and Jerioth: and these were her sons; Jasar, and Subab, and Ardon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:19",
      "text": "And Gazuba died; and Chaleb took to himself Ephrath, and she bore to him Or.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:20",
      "text": "And Or begot Uri, and Uri begot Beseleel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:21",
      "text": "And after this Esron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Galaad, and he took her when he was sixty-five years old; and she bore him Seruch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:22",
      "text": "And Seruch begot Jair, and he had twenty-three cities in Galaad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:23",
      "text": "And he took Gedsur and Aram, the towns of Jair from them; with Canath and its towns, sixty cities. All these belonged to the sons of Machir the father of Galaad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:24",
      "text": "And after the death of Esron, Chaleb came to Ephratha; and the wife of Esron was Abia; and she bore him Ascho the father of Thecoe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:25",
      "text": "And the sons of Jerameel the first-born of Esron were, the first-born Ram, and Banaa, and Aram, and Asan his brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:26",
      "text": "And Jerameel had another wife, and her name was Atara: she is the mother of Ozom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:27",
      "text": "And the sons of Ram the first-born of Jerameel were Maas, and Jamin, and Acor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:28",
      "text": "And the sons of Ozom were, Samai, and Jadae: and the sons of Samai; Nadab, and Abisur.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:29",
      "text": "And the name of the wife of Abisur was Abichaia, and she bore him Achabar, and Moel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:30",
      "text": "And the sons of Nadab; Salad and Apphain; and Salad died without children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:31",
      "text": "And the sons of Apphain, Isemiel; and the sons of Isemiel, Sosan; and the sons of Sosan, Dadai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:32",
      "text": "And the sons of Dadai, Achisamas, Jether, Jonathan: and Jether died childless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:33",
      "text": "And the sons of Jonathan; Phaleth, and Hozam. These were the sons of Jerameel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:34",
      "text": "And Sosan had no sons, but daughters. And Sosan had an Egyptian servant, and his name was Jochel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:35",
      "text": "And Sosan gave his daughter to Jochel his servant to wife; and she bore him Ethi.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.36",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:36",
      "text": "And Ethi begot Nathan, and Nathan begot Zabed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.37",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:37",
      "text": "and Zabed begot Aphamel, and Aphamel begot Obed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.38",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:38",
      "text": "And Obed begot Jeu, and Jeu begot Azarias.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.39",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:39",
      "text": "And Azarias begot Chelles, and Chelles begot Eleasa,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.40",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:40",
      "text": "and Eleasa begot Sosomai, and Sosomai begot Salum,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.41",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:41",
      "text": "and Salum begot Jechemias, and Jechemias begot Elisama, and Elisama begot Ismael.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.42",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:42",
      "text": "And the sons of Chaleb the brother of Jerameel were, Marisa his first-born, he is the father of Ziph:—and the sons of Marisa the father of Chebron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.43",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:43",
      "text": "And the sons of Chebron; Core, and Thapphus, and Recom, and Samaa.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.44",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:44",
      "text": "And Samaa begot Raem the father of Jeclan: and Jeclan begot Samai.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.45",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:45",
      "text": "And his son was Maon: and Maon is the father of Baethsur.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.46",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:46",
      "text": "And Gaepha the concubine of Chaleb bore Aram, and Mosa, and Gezue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.47",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:47",
      "text": "And the sons of Addai were Ragem, and Joatham, and Sogar, and Phalec, and Gaepha, and Sagae.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.48",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:48",
      "text": "And Chaleb’s concubine Mocha bore Saber, and Tharam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.49",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:49",
      "text": "She bore also Sagae the father of Madmena, and Sau the father of Machabena, and the father of Gaebal: and the daughter of Chaleb was Ascha.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.50",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:50",
      "text": "These were the sons of Chaleb: the sons of Or the first-born of Ephratha; Sobal the father of Cariathiarim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.51",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:51",
      "text": "Salomon the father of Baetha, Lammon the father of Baethalaem, and Arim the father of Bethgedor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.52",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:52",
      "text": "And the sons of Sobal the father of Cariathiarim were Araa, and Æsi, and Ammanith,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.53",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:53",
      "text": "and Umasphae, cities of Jair; Æthalim, and Miphithim, and Hesamathim, and Hemasaraim; from these went forth the Sarathaeans, and the sons of Esthaam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.54",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:54",
      "text": "The sons of Salomon; Baethalaem, the Netophathite, Ataroth of the house of Joab, and half of the family of Malathi, Esari.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:first-chronicles.2.55",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 2:55",
      "text": "The families of the scribes dwelling in Jabis; Thargathiim, and Samathiim, and Sochathim, these are the Kinaeans that came of Hemath, the father of the house of Rechab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
